The paper deals with natural language processing and transfer learning, which are typically covered under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of transformer-based models and masked language modeling suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The evaluation of the approach on cross-lingual classification benchmarks and a new Cross-lingual Question Answering Dataset (XQuAD) may also make it relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the mention of using deep learning models for natural language processing suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
